> Please also take a look at the vs-arm64 build failure.

@saiarcot895 can you please help in understanding why the below config is not getting set at debian/build/build_arm64_none_arm64/.config when compiling for vs-arm64. It passes for pensando-arm64. Is there any place where we are including configs for vs?
CONFIG_RTC_DRV_ELBA_CPLD

> @bmridul any reference for this claim: `UBIFS does not work on NOR Flash with small sector erasesize`

@prgeor , I have put a [link](https://cateee.net/lkddb/web-lkddb/MTD_SPI_NOR_USE_4K_SECTORS.html) to the man  page for the kernel config in PR description. There itself this issue is mentioned. 

    Please note that some tools/drivers/filesystems may not work with 4096 B erase size (e.g. UBIFS requires 15 KiB as a minimum).

@saiarcot895  Understood and agree. The comment you are referring to was from our previous version of the DTS that we tried to upstream.
We have modified the DTS to address most of Andrew's comments in this version of the DTS as much as our platform supports. 
Thank you for help with review and merging
